    <h3>Sofia</h3>
    <p>Last year Sofia was voted the host for Euruko 2016. It's the capital of Bulgaria, and also the largest city in the country.
      It's located right in the centre of the Balkan Peninsula, at the foot of Vitosha mountain.
      With more than 7000 years of history it's one of the oldest cities in Europe. </p>

    <p>One can easily find their way around Sofia by means of the Sofia Underground, which sports two lines and 34 stations. It makes possible traveling between the city center and the airport in around 30 minutes for less than 1 euro. After visiting all the historical and cultural sights in the city center, attendees can enjoy a walk in Sofiaâ€™s many parks and gardens, such as South Park, Borisova Garden or even the Vitosha Mountain National Park.</p>
