    <h3>The Venue</h3>

    <p>The National Palace of Culture, is located at the heart of Sofia.
      It was built in 1981, to serve as a conference and exhibition center for various events.
      Its vast exhibition spaces, its numerous halls, and the wide views from its spacious balconies contribute to its popularity as an event center to this day.</p>

    <p>The area around NDK is a spacious square, popular among young people, displaying their skating and biking skills, couples enjoying ice-cream or pizza at the benches, and kids playing in the small park.
      One of Sofia's vibrant pedestrian streets - Vitosha, is just a few minutes walk from the venue.</p>

    <p>There is a subway station, which conveniently exits at the venue entrance, and near the near end to Vitosha street.
      The subway exits are connected to NDK's underground.</p>

